  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You briefly stop the flow of time for everyone but yourself. No time passes for other creatures, while you take your spellcasting ability modifier number of turns in a row, during which you can use actions and move as normal.</p><p>This spell ends if one of the actions you use during this period, or any effects that you create during it, affects a creature other than you or an object being worn or carried by someone other than you. In addition, the spell ends if you move to a place more than 1,000 feet from the location where you cast it.</p><p>Once the spell ends, the interrupted action immediately is resolved. The effects of your turns taken while time was stopped may affect the results of that action as the DM deems appropriate.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
